    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-09-14T10:44:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-09-14T10:44:00-05:00" n="475"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d475">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 862.85/150</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Uruguay</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_JRE1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jeffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-09-14T12:00:00-03:44">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 14, 1917, 12 noon</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 6 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Police authorities of port of Montevideo to-day have placed all German ships
                    under police control. Rumors of possible injury to ships is the reason assigned
                    for this action. Germans have been taken off ships.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_JRE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jeffery</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
